section_text:
The table below allows users of this Code to quickly and accurately determine what
            ordinances have been considered for codification in each supplement. Ordinances that
            are of a general and permanent nature are codified in the Code and are considered
            "Included." Ordinances that are not of a general and permanent nature are not codified
            in the Code and are considered "Omitted."
            
         
            In addition, by adding to this table with each supplement, users of this Code of Ordinances
            will be able to gain a more complete picture of the Code's historical evolution.
